diff --git a/kanecta-mcp/SETUP-NOTES.md b/kanecta-mcp/SETUP-NOTES.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..a433c07
--- /dev/null
+++ b/kanecta-mcp/SETUP-NOTES.md
@@ -0,0 +1,154 @@
+# kanecta-mcp Setup Notes
+
+Notes from getting the MCP server working locally for the first time. Documents bugs found, fixes applied, and the full Claude Code MCP configuration journey.
+
+---
+
+## Bugs Fixed
+
+### 1. `new Datastore(path)` → `Datastore.open(path)`
+
+**Error:** `TypeError: this._adapter.getDataRoot is not a function`
+
+The `Datastore` constructor takes an **adapter instance**, not a path string. Passing a path string meant `this._adapter` was a string, so no methods existed on it.
+
+```js
+// Wrong
+return { ds: new Datastore(p), cfg };
+
+// Right
+return { ds: Datastore.open(p), cfg };
+```
+
+The same bug existed in `kanecta-api/src/app.js` and was fixed there too.
+
+### 2. `@kanecta/lib` was pointing to the published npm package
+
+**Error:** `getDataRoot is not a function` (even after fix #1 in the MCP server)
+
+The published `@kanecta/lib@1.0.0` on npm was missing `getDataRoot()` and other recent additions. The local source had them but the MCP server was pulling the stale published version.
+
+**Fix:** Change `package.json` to use a local file reference:
+
+```json
+"@kanecta/lib": "file:../kanecta-lib"
+```
+
+Then `npm install` to re-link. This is the same pattern already used by `kanecta-api`.
+
+### 3. Hand-rolled MCP protocol didn't handle `ping`
+
+**Error:** `MCP error -32000: Connection closed`
+
+The original `src/index.js` implemented the MCP protocol manually over stdin/stdout. Claude Code sends periodic `ping` messages to verify liveness — unhandled messages caused the connection to be dropped.
+
+**Fix:** Rewrote `src/index.js` to use the official `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk`:
+
+```js
+const { McpServer } = require('@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/mcp.js');
+const { StdioServerTransport } = require('@modelcontextprotocol/sdk/server/stdio.js');
+const { z } = require('zod');
+```
+
+The SDK handles `ping`, `initialize`, protocol negotiation, and all other transport-level concerns correctly.
+
+**Note:** `@modelcontextprotocol/sdk` is an ESM package (`"type": "module"`), but Node.js v22+ supports `require()` of ESM modules, so CJS files can load it directly.
+
+---
+
+## Claude Code MCP Configuration
+
+### Config file location
+
+Claude Code reads MCP server config from **`~/.claude.json`** under the `mcpServers` key — **not** `~/.claude/settings.json` as you might expect.
+
+```json
+// ~/.claude.json
+{
+  "mcpServers": {
+    "kanecta": {
+      "type": "stdio",
+      "command": "/home/<user>/.nvm/versions/node/<version>/bin/node",
+      "args": ["/path/to/kanecta-mcp/src/index.js"],
+      "env": {
+        "KANECTA_DATASTORE": "/home/<user>/.kanecta"
+      }
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+### Project-level config overrides global config
+
+`~/.claude.json` also has a `projects` key with per-project settings. If a project has its own `mcpServers` entry, it **overrides** the global one for that project directory.
+
+The kanecta project had this entry (likely created when the server was first added via the UI):
+
+```json
+"projects": {
+  "/home/<user>/code/kanecta": {
+    "mcpServers": {
+      "kanecta": {
+        "type": "stdio",
+        "command": "npx",
+        "args": ["-y", "@kanecta/mcp"],
+        "env": {}
+      }
+    }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+This was pointing to the published npm package via `npx`, which failed (outdated package, or registry auth issues). The project-level entry must also be updated to point to the local source.
+
+### Node path when using nvm
+
+Claude Code launches MCP server processes without a full login shell, so nvm's shims are not on PATH. Using `node` as the command will fail silently.
+
+**Use the full absolute path to node:**
+
+```
+/home/<user>/.nvm/versions/node/<version>/bin/node
+```
+
+Find yours with: `which node`
+
+---
+
+## Datastore Initialisation
+
+Before the MCP server can be used, a datastore must be initialised. Use the CLI:
+
+```bash
+kanecta init ~/.kanecta --owner your@email.com
+```
+
+Or via node directly if the CLI isn't on PATH:
+
+```bash
+node /path/to/kanecta-cli/index.js init ~/.kanecta --owner your@email.com
+```
+
+The `KANECTA_DATASTORE` env var must point to this directory.
+
+---
+
+## Suggested Improvements
+
+### Setup script
+
+A `scripts/setup.sh` that:
+1. Runs `npm install` in `kanecta-mcp` (and `kanecta-lib`, `kanecta-filesystem`)
+2. Initialises the datastore if `~/.kanecta` doesn't exist
+3. Patches `~/.claude.json` with the correct project-level MCP config (both global `mcpServers` and the project entry under `projects[cwd]`)
+4. Prints instructions to restart Claude Code
+
+### README additions
+
+- Document that `@kanecta/lib` must be installed via `file:` link (not npm) for local development
+- Document the `KANECTA_DATASTORE` env var requirement
+- Document the `~/.claude.json` config structure with a copy-paste example using full node path
+
+### Consider compiling to `dist/`
+
+The working `landonline-db` MCP server compiles TypeScript to `dist/index.js` — a single self-contained file with no local `file:` symlink dependencies. This avoids the `new Datastore(path)` vs `Datastore.open(path)` style issues and makes the config simpler (no `KANECTA_DATASTORE` env var needed if the datastore path is baked into config discovery logic).
